task.summary: Default task
Finished project setup Added first unit test for cloud endpoints
Refactored unit tests. Started adding functionallity to add friendships
Fixed test-preparation
updated gitignore
Added methods to look for friends of a specific user Added test for friendships

Reworked authentication of App. Firebase is now implemented again and currently allows creating users with an eMail and Password and loging them in. (Even though the UI does not support that right now)
Implemented FirebaseUI for login
Minor changes
Started working on the addFriend activity
Some more untested work on adding users as friends
Some further work on friendship requests
Fixed the smartphone not being able to connect to the server.
Finally fully implemented Firebase-Authentication.
Minor fixes
Fixed small crash on wrong button click
Refactored a sample ApiCall. Future Api calls can be performed in a similar (elegant) way.
Implement the SearchView
Started work on user creation. After the user has logged in using an email and password he fills in some data to create a DoryUser on the server side
Refactored one more ApiCall
Fixed threading issues. The client can now check whether a DoryUser with the ID exists. If not an activity is started that is supposed to allow creating a new user.
Users can now be created. There's still something not working as intended though...
A user is now prompted to create a user account if it does not exist on login
Fixed crash if there was no user logged in
It is now possible to search for other users in the AddFriendActivity
Some files that might not have been commited earlier (sorry!)
It is now no longer possible to send a friend request to oneself
Added some security fixes and error checks to the backend
